news.title: Signatureglobal (India) net profit up 48.17% in Q4 FY25
news.para: Signatureglobal (India) net consolidated total income stood at ₹570.43 crore, a dip of 21.07 per cent from ₹722.73 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Noida authority slaps notice on Sector 44 RWA for offering club membership with false claims
news.para: According to the notice, the RWA misrepresented the Authority's sanctioned plan by showing an area earmarked for car parking as a huge green belt, giving the impression of luxurious facilities for the members.

news.title: Eternal leases office space across seven floors in Mumbai’s Andheri
news.para: The company has entered into a licensing agreement with Runwal Realty subsidiary Histyle Retail for this office premises spanning across total seven floors of a commercial tower R Square in J B Nagar locality.

news.title: Somany Ceramics eyes bathware revenue of ₹600 crore in four years; expects consolidation in tiles sector
news.para: In conversation with ETRealty, Abhishek Somany, managing director & CEO of Somany Ceramics talked about the company's performance in FY25, market outlook, ESG practices, and expansion strategy in bathware and adhesives.

news.title: Developers expand senior living footprint as occupancy, lifestyle preferences drive growth
news.para: Capgemini’s findings show 46% of Indian seniors are prioritizing experiences over real estate upgrades, indicating a strong tailwind for senior living models focused on community, convenience, and health infrastructure. ​​​​

news.title: Four Indian REITs distribute ₹1,553 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: For the full financial year 2024–25, the cumulative distribution by the four REITs reached ₹6,070 crore, up from ₹5,366 crore in FY24, reflecting a strong and consistent over 13% year-on-year growth.

news.title: Maharashtra govt promotes artificial sand to conserve environment, boost construction sector
news.para: This follows a policy to encourage the use of artificial sand, in a bid to prevent environmental hazards due to excessive extraction of sand from river banks.

news.title: Sand stock plenty for development work: Bihar deputy CM
news.para: Sinha said sand pits are closed every year from June 15 due to the monsoon, but the state govt has arranged sufficient stock of sand in advance to complete development projects on time.

news.title: Shapoorji Pallonji Real Estate, KREEVA & ASK Property Fund launch residential project in Gurugram
news.para: The project is expected to generate projected top-line revenues of over ₹1,400 crore over the next five years.

news.title: Vapi gets its first-ever draft town planning scheme approved
news.para: Until now, no TP scheme had been approved during the tenure of the Vapi municipality, which was formed in 1995. The VMC came into existence in Jan 2025 and has now taken its first steps toward structured city planning.

news.title: Two stalled housing projects in Noida back on track
news.para: The NCR-based property developers have started development work on over 1.5 million sq ft of space after clearing the dues of the lenders and the state urban development authority.

news.title: Gurugram: Illegal buildings & walls built on 18 acres razed in DTCP drive
news.para: Developers had allegedly started unauthorised plotting and construction in violation of urban planning regulations in three villages, Karanki, Sancholi and Daulha.

news.title: ED searches at 13 locations in Vasai-Virar over illegal buildings case
news.para: The developers constructed these buildings using falsified documents, fabricated approvals and fraudulent sale agreements, the ED said.

news.title: Odisha government plans to overhaul resettlement & rehabilitation policy
news.para: After the meeting, revenue minister Suresh Pujari said many private industries acquired more plots than needed and could not utilise them properly, even after 10-15 years.

news.title: Hyderabad development body pushes land pooling schemes to boost revenue
news.para: According to HMDA sources, land pooling initiatives covering approximately 300 acres are currently being developed in Pratap Singaram, Lemur, and Inmulnarva (near Kothur).

news.title: Government appoints Odisha RERA chairperson, two other members
news.para: Asit Kumar Mohapatra was appointed as ORERA chairman, while Rajendra Mishra and Shyam Sundar Dash will join as the other two members.

news.title: Delhi civic body identifies commercial users paying residential tax
news.para: Aiming to increase its tax collection for the financial year 2025-26 and identify defaulters, the civic body is referencing the electricity bills generated by the power discoms.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government to cap registration fee for rent agreements
news.para: The department of stamp and registration is working on a proposal to reduce and cap the registration amount for lease deeds. The changes are being considered in light of the existing rules, under which registration is an expensive exercise.

news.title: Haryana government backs HC order to act against unauthorised construction in DLF areas
news.para: ​SC is likely to deliver a ruling next week in the case. The verdict is likely to have far-reaching consequences for thousands of residents and commercial establishments in one of the city's most prominent residential areas.

news.title: Telengana RERA penalises builder for nine-year delay in handing over villa to owners
news.para: The complainants – Neelima Vanamala and Srikanth Leburu, residents of Tellapur – had booked Villa No. 113 in Oct 2014 for a total cost of 73.4 lakh.
